value.value: The most widely spoken of the Turkic languages, spoken as an official language in Turkey, Northern Cyprus, and Cyprus.
A Polynesian language spoken as the official language of Tuvalu.
A dialect of the Niger-Congo Akan language spoken by the Ashanti people in southern and central Ghana.
A Turkic language spoken in the Republic of Tuva in south-central Siberia in Russia.
A Uralic language spoken by the Udmurt people of the Russian constituent republic of Udmurtia.
A Turkic language spoken primarily by the Uyghur people in the Xinjiang Uyghur Autonomous Region of Western China.
An Indo-European East Slavic language that is the official state language of the Ukraine.
A Niger-Congo Bantu language spoken by the Ovimbundu people of Angola.
A Persianized standard register of the Hindustani language that is the official national language of Pakistan.
A Turkic language that is the sole official language of Uzbekistan.
The use of any device, marker, or other means for the purpose of detecting the presence of disease, usually in asymptomatic individuals.
A Niger-Congo Mande language spoken by the Vai people in Liberia and Sierra Leone.
A Niger-Congo Bantu language mainly spoken by the Venda people in the northern part of South Africa's Limpopo Province, as well as by some Lemba people in Zimbabwe.
A Uralic language spoken by the Vote people of the Ingria area of Finland.
An Afro-Asiatic language spoken in the Wolayita Zone and some other parts of the Southern Nations, Nationalities, and People's Region of Ethiopia.
An Austronesian language native to Eastern Visayas of the Philippines.
A Native American language isolate spoken by the Washo people in the area of the California-Nevada border, especially around Lake Tahoe.
A Romance language that is spoken in the Wallonia region in Belgium and some villages of Northern France.
A Niger-Congo language spoken by the Wolof people of Senegal, the Gambia, and Mauritania.
A Mongolic language that is regarded as either a dialect of Mongolian or a distinct language.

A semisynthetic water-soluble derivative of the antineoplastic antibiotic duocarmycin B2.  Activated by carboxyl esterase, pibrozelesin alkylates DNA by binding to adenine-thymine (A-T)-rich sequences in the minor groove of DNA, thereby inhibiting DNA replication and inducing apoptosis.
Therapeutic use of hypnotism by a clinical professional.
A Niger-Congo Bantu language spoken as an official language in South Africa and Zimbabwe.
A Niger-Congo Bantu language spoken mainly in Malawi, Tanzania, and Mozambique.
An Austronesian language spoken by the people on the island of Yap, Federated States of Micronesia.
A High German-based vernacular fused with elements taken from Hebrew and Aramaic as well as from Slavic languages and traces of Romance languages.
A Niger-Congo language spoken in West Africa.
A group of around 50 closely related indigenous Mesoamerican languages spoken by the Zapotec people from the southwestern-central highlands of Mexico.
An Afro-Asiatic Berber language spoken from the town of Mederdra in southwestern Mauritania to the Atlantic coast and in Senegal.
The standardized national variety of Berber spoken in Morocco.
Any of more than a dozen Tai languages spoken by the Zhuang people of southern China in the province of Guangxi and adjacent parts of Yunnan and Guangdong.
A Niger-Congo Bantu language spoken by the Zulu people of South Africa.
After menopause.
A language of the Zuni people, indigenous to western New Mexico and eastern Arizona in the United States.
An Indo-European language spoken primarily in eastern Turkey by the Zaza people.
A regimen consisting of bendamustine and obinutuzumab that can be used in the treatment of chronic lymphocytic leukemia (CLL) and small lymphocytic lymphoma (SLL).

A regimen consisting of cyclophosphamide, doxorubicin, vincristine, prednisone (CHOP) and obinutuzumab that can be used in the treatment of some forms of non-Hodgkin lymphoma (NHL), including follicular lymphoma, gastric and nongastric MALT lymphomas, nodal marginal zone lymphoma (NMZL) and splenic marginal zone lymphoma (SMZL).

A regimen consisting of cyclophosphamide, etoposide, prednisone, procarbazine (CEPP) and rituximab that can be used in the treatment of some forms of non-Hodgkin lymphoma (NHL), including diffuse large B-cell lymphoma (DLBCL), and post-transplant lymphoproliferative disorders.

A regimen consisting of rituximab, cyclophosphamide, liposomal doxorubicin, vincristine and prednisone (R-CDOP) that can be used in the treatment of some forms of non-Hodgkin lymphoma (NHL), including diffuse large B-cell lymphoma (DLBCL).

An immunohistochemical screening panel for Burkitt lymphoma consisting of reagents that identify the cell-surface presence of: CD3, CD10, CD20, CD45, Ki-67, BCL2, BCL6, and TdT (terminal deoxynucleotide transferase).

label.value: Flow Cytometry Panel for Burkitt Lymphoma

value.value: A flow cytometry screening panel for Burkitt lymphoma consisting of reagents that identify the cell-surface presence of: CD3, CD5, CD10, CD19, CD20, CD45, TdT (terminal deoxynucleotide transferase), and kappa or lambda light chains.

A regimen consisting of chlorambucil and rituximab that can be used in the treatment of some forms of non-Hodgkin lymphoma (NHL), including follicular lymphoma, gastric and nongastric mucosa-associated lymphoid tissue (MALT) lymphoma, nodal and splenic marginal zone lymphoma, and chronic lymphocytic leukemia (CLL).

Physical exercise that uses weight, or other forms of resistance, to induce muscle contraction and build strength, anaerobic endurance, and size of skeletal muscles. Typical exercises include leg and chest press, knee extension, leg curl, row, abdominal crunch, and bicep curl.
Movement of residence from one place to another. Includes nomadism; labor or seasonal migration; patterns of rural, urban, or suburban migration; or voluntary or forced relocation. (PSY94)

Classes consisting of didactics, class discussion, and guided meditation practice designed to challenge unexamined assumptions regarding feelings and actions toward others with a focus on generating spontaneous empathy and compassion for self and others.
A gastric adenocarcinoma that is not amenable to surgical resection.
A rare condition characterized by hyperplasia and hypertrophy of the pituitary gland. It is caused by hypersecretion of hypothalamic stimulating hormones.
An individual receiving a cord blood transplant.
A peripheral neural block of the medial and lateral pectoral nerves.
A physical exercise in which a specific muscle or tendon is deliberately flexed or stretched in order to improve the muscle's elasticity.
